8 prohibited acts; violations and penalties
9 A. As used in this Part, the following words shall have the meanings ascribed
10 to them in this Section unless the context clearly indicates otherwise:
11 (1) "Advanced driver assistance system" means any motor vehicle electronic
12 safety system, as detailed in the applicable version of SAE International's SAE J3016
13 Levels of Driving Automation, or its relevant successor, that is designed to support
14 the driver and motor vehicle in a manner intended to increase motor vehicle safety
15 and reduce losses associated with motor vehicle crashes.
16 (2) "Motor vehicle glass" means the glass and non-glass parts associated
17 with the replacement of the glass used in the windshield, doors, or windows of a
18 motor vehicle.
19 (3) "Motor vehicle glass repair shop" means any person, including the
20 person's employees and agents, that for compensation engages in the repair or
21 replacement of damaged motor vehicle glass.
22 (4) "Repair or replacement of motor vehicle glass" means and includes but
23 is not limited to the inspection, repairing, restoring, or replacing of damaged motor
24 vehicle glass and the calibrating or recalibrating of an advanced driver assistance
25 system when an incident requires the replacement of damaged motor vehicle glass.
26 B. A motor vehicle glass repair shop or any other person who is
27 compensated for the solicitation of insurance claims shall not engage in any of the
28 following unfair trade practices:
29 (1) Offer a rebate, gift, gift card, cash, coupon, fee, prize, bonus, payment,
30 incentive, inducement, or any other thing of value to any insured, insurance
